annotations:
I guess that some things change
 I guess I don’t need you at all
This felt like the final release! Finally letting go of that person and who I used to be. Letting go of resentment and the past!

It was miserable and it was beautiful
 But I don’t think I really want it that way

This is about the tendency to romanticize passionate, crazy relationships. I think for the longest time I’ve seen healthy relationships as boring – and this is just facing the I don’t really think I want something that is so miserable even if it is beautiful at times.

Drove 2000 miles
 And when the sun hit me
 Didn’t mind you weren’t with me
 It kinda made me happy

I drove across the country to move from Nashville to Los Angeles. It took about four days and I just remember feeling the heaviness leave my body as the excitement of a new life in California come in. I finally felt true happiness and excitement for the first time in a while.

You were miserable, I lost my colorful
 I didn’t notice when the world turned grey
The idea of giving it everything and trying to fix a person just sucking all the life out of you. I see life in color – but sometimes in a dependent relationship you can lose the vibrance.

Even if hell could freeze
 I’d just sit by myself and turn blue

I was sick of having all of these feelings for someone who I felt like just pitied me for having them. It was definitely the point of hitting the wall of being over it. I really like the play on the phrase “when hell freezes over”. I pictured my stubborn self just sitting in a ball in a corner of hell getting hypothermia before ever letting this person get to me again.

description.plain: I wrote “Talking to Myself” eight days before heading to the studio with Michelle Buzz out in LA. We were talking about how in long term relationships you get so used to the other person being around – the song is about once the relationship has ended and the moments you forget that they’re not there anymore. You know, those few seconds where you forget that you broke up and you just want to tell them all about your day or something funny that happened. Those moments create a sense of loneliness and craziness because that person isn’t around anymore, and so you end up just talking to yourself.

We were talking about how in long term relationships you get so used to the other person being around – the song is about once the relationship has ended and the moments you forget that they’re not there anymore. You know, those few seconds where you forget that you broke up and you just want to tell them all about your day or something funny that happened. Those moments create a sense of loneliness and craziness because that person isn’t around anymore, and so you end up just talking to yourself.

annotations:
He knows I’m going down, so he’s just counting up all my mistakes
 He says I’m difficult, well, yes, of course I am fuckin’ insane

I wrote this section when we were recording the final vocals in the studio because I felt like the song needed more. I originally had ‘for goodness sake” instead of “fucking insane” and on first pass through Konrad thought I said fucking insane and was laughing. Never changed a lyric so quick. The final I … I … I is just me kind of being at a loss for words and feels like the climax of the song.
I want all of my old lovers to be thinking of me on their dying day

When the 50th Anniversary of Joni Mitchell’s album Blue came along I was reading an article where several respected songwriters were quoted saying that they had been in a relationship with Joni and how to this day they are still in love with her and haven’t fully gotten over her. And I thought that was badass.
Last summer I kissed one of his exes, turns out she’s really gay
True story.
He’s terrified that I’m in love with him if I ask him to stay (Ha, ha, ha)
I added the laughing at the end of the line because I always use humor as a coping mechanism.

What must it take?
 Who will be the first to break?

The chorus was the hardest lyrically to find. I at first just mumbled these lyrics as a placeholder but ended up keeping them because I liked the idea of it being the more vulnerable moment/question in the song.
So I’d rather go to bed alone and let him touch himself thinking of me
This lyric is just about how I’d rather you desire me than actually have me.
I’ve spent one too many times being brushed aside after he gets what he needs
Just the idea of feeling used in hookup culture.

He said that I should teach a masterclass on how to be a tease
 I just hate the mornings where I’m using my finger to brush my teeth

The song started with these two lines I had written in my notes app for a few weeks. I was seeing this person who would jokingly call me a tease. One time I responded how I didn’t have a toothbrush so I had to go home.
